The paper deals with a downlink multiuser MIMO system employing regularized zero-forcing precoding. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) as it deals with the transmission and processing of information. The paper also discusses the optimization of user loading for spectral efficiency, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of massive MIMO systems and the analysis of the asymptotic signal-to-leakage-plus-noise ratio (SLNR) falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the optimization of user loading, which can be considered a machine learning problem (cs.LG).
